'''AIDS'''

# Acquired Immune Deficiency Syndrome,  an infectious [[disease]] which causes gradual degeneration of the body's [[immune system]].  Caused by the [[HIV]] virus, it is transmitted mainly through infected blood or sex with an infected person.  As of 2005 AIDS is still incurable; although certain drugs and treatments are known to hamper its progress, victims will usually die after a number of years.

